    <h2 id= "Amala">Amala and Ewedu</h2>

    <img src="https://i.pinimg.com/originals/a0/13/23/a0132382c1bcd9ee0225ce95e2834a3e.jpg" alt="Amala and Ewedu" width="600px">
<p>Recipe for Amala</p>
<p>Amala is the dark colored <em>swallow</em> that you eat with Ewedu and stew. When <em>coupled</em> with the right soup assitants, Amala is a great game changer.<br>
You turn the flour in hot water and mix until it's smooth enough.</p>
<table>
    <thead>
        <tr>
            <th>Ingredients</th>
            <th>Quantity</th>
        </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>Yam Flour</td>
        <td>Two cups</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Water</td>
        <td>One and a half cups</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
</table>
    <p>Ewedu</p>
    <p>Ewedu is green and slimy. it <em>"draws"</em> when cooked properly, aids the unobstructed movement of the Amala.</p>
<br>
<table>
    <thead>
        <tr>
